<DIV1 TYPE="argument">
<PB REF="4">
<HEAD>The ARGUMENT.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">The Departure of Uly&s;&s;es from Calyp&s;o.</HEAD>
<P>Pallas <HI>in a Council of the Gods complains of the Detention of</HI> Uly&s;&s;es <HI>in
the I&s;land of</HI> Calyp&s;o; <HI>whereupon</HI> Mercury <HI>is &s;ent to command
his removal. The &s;eat of</HI> Calyp&s;o <HI>de&s;crib'd. She con&s;ents with
much difficulty, and</HI> Uly&s;&s;es <HI>builds a ve&s;&s;el with his own hands,
on which he embarks.</HI> Neptune <HI>overtakes him with a terrible
tempe&s;t, in which he is &s;hipwreck'd, and in the la&s;t danger of
death; 'till</HI> Leucothea <HI>a Sea Godde&s;s a&s;&s;i&s;ts him, and after innu|merable
perils, he gets a&s;hore on</HI> Phaeacia.</P>
