Then Envy grieves, with inly-pining Hate;<MILESTONE N="225"></L>
<L>The good exult, and heav'n is in our &s;tate.</L>
<L>To whom the Nymph: O &s;tranger cea&s;e thy care,</L>
<L>Wife is thy &s;oul, but man is born to bear:</L>
<L><HI>Jove</HI> weighs affairs of earth in dubious &s;cales,</L>
<L>And the good &s;uffers, while the bad prevails:<MILESTONE N="230"></L>
<L>Bear, with a &s;oul re&s;ign'd, the will of <HI>Jove;</HI></L>
<L>Who breathes, mu&s;t mourn: thy woes are from above.</L>
<L>But &s;ince thou tread'&s;t our ho&s;pitable &s;hore,</L>
<L>'Tis mine to bid the wretched grieve no more,</L>
<L>To cloath the naked, and thy way to guide&mdash;<MILESTONE N="235"></L>
