<L><PB N="84" REF="83">
<MILESTONE N="325">They ru&s;h into the deep with eager joy,</L>
<L>Climb the &s;teep &s;urge, and thro' the tempe&s;t fly;</L>
<L>A proud, unpoli&s;h'd race&mdash;To me belongs</L>
<L>The care to &s;hun the bla&s;t of &s;land'rous tongues;</L>
<L>Le&s;t malice, prone the virtuous to defame,</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="330">Thus with vile cen&s;ure taint my &s;potle&s;s name.</L>
<L>&startq;What &s;tranger this, whom thus <HI>Nau&s;icaa</HI> leads?</L>
<L>Heav'ns! with what graceful maje&s;ty he treads?</L>
