<L>While the &s;low mules draw on th' imperial maid:</L>
<L>Thro' the proud &s;treet &s;he moves, the publick gaze;</L>
<L>The turning wheel before the Palace &s;tays.</L>
<L>With ready love her brothers gath'ring round,<MILESTONE N="5"></L>
<L>Receiv'd the ve&s;tures, and the mules unbound.</L>
<L><PB N="124" REF="120">
She &s;eeks the bridal bow'r: A matron there</L>
<L>The ri&s;ing fire &s;upplies with bu&s;y care,</L>
<L>Who&s;e charms in youth her father's heart inflam'd,</L>
<L><MILESTONE N="10">Now worn with age, <HI>Eurymedu&s;a</HI> nam'd:</L>
<L>The captive dame <HI>Phaeacian</HI> rovers bore,</L>
